      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">1. Managing Workforce Diversity.</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The department is overwhelmed with reports of issues like harassment, discrimination, and other human rights violations. This has been attributed to the increasing diversity in the workforce. It is, however, the duty of those working in this department to ensure that these issues are resolved to make an organization a peaceful working place.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">2. Maintaining the Productivity of Employees.</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">It is the responsibility of the human resource team to hire competent staffers. The team is in charge of keeping the employees productive by motivating them. Data suggest that the Human resource department enhances the employees' productivity by creating a culture that is inspiring and encouraging the workforce. The challenge of maintaining the productivity levels most affects companies with a significant human resource.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3 mt-6">3. Preparing Aspiring Leaders for management-level Roles.</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The HR department is mandated to prepare inspiring and competent leaders for management-level responsibilities. For this to happen, an organization needs to provide the necessary training to future managers through its human resource unit, which proves to be an appealing task.</p>
    </section>
